window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Medical research has shown that pain resides in both the body and the mind, and that how you focus your attention and awareness can make all the difference. With <i>Pain Relief</i>, Shinzen Young teaches listeners how to step outside of pain through traditional meditation practices. Drawing from 20 years of results in the field, this widely respected teacher offers a practical program to address both chronic and short-term pain, possibly reducing the need for drugs or surgery. Step-by-step techniques taught in plain language show how to overcome internal resistance, the key to transforming physical pain into a flow of pure energy. Includes four guided practices that listeners can use anywhere.</p>"; 
